betterquesting:10.desc:8:
If you are totally new to Modded Minecraft, congratulations on opening this book! Let's learn how to use it.

As part of each quest in this book, you must complete one or more tasks, of which there are several possible types. The First, and simplest, is the Checkbox Task. To complete this task, all you have to do is check the box. The Second, and most common, is the retrieval task. For this, you must have a certain number of a certain item or set of items in your inventory, and you must have them all at once. Let's try it out with six wooden logs. This type of task may require you to submit the items, when it says "Consume: Yes" at the top. Collect some more logs and submit them to try it out.

There is also the crafting task, which requires you to have crafted a certain number of items. Make some planks to try it out.

Congratulations, you now know the basics of the quest book! For completing all four tasks in this quest, you may have some food and torches. Click the "Claim" button below to claim your reward!

In this modpack, we have two very important quality of life mods: Just Enough Items and The One Probe.
Just Enough Items is an item and recipe viewing mod. It is responsible for the item menu on the right side of your inventory. JEI’s features are achieved with keybinds. 
Pressing R will allow you to see all recipes for a specific item. Many items have multiple recipes, but some only have one. In the top right corner of some recipes you may see a small shuffle icon, this means the recipe is Shapeless and the items can be placed anywhere in the Crafting Grid. In the bottom right side of the recipe, you will see a + icon. Clicking it will, if you have the items in your inventory, move the items into the crafting grid for you for one recipe. Shift-clicking it will do the same but move the most items it can to make the most crafting recipes it can. If you don’t have the items in your inventory, it will tell what items you are currently missing.
Pressing U will allow you to find all uses for a specific item, as an example, if you hit U on an iron ingot, you will see the recipe for an Iron sword, chestplate, etc.

The One Probe is a UI improvement mod that adds block information directly into the game for you, with an unobtrusive tooltip on the top of your screen. TOP will display information about what a block contains as well, if it is a chest or storage block, it will display that knowledge. If it is an RF-based machine, it will display the items inside, RF Storage, and the RF/t usage. If it a liquid storage block, known as a tank, it will display how many buckets of that liquid you have in the block.
The Nether Provides a vast array of resources that are not available in the overworld. How about you go gather some of them?
In addition to providing a much more reliable source of Ender Pearls, the End now also contains Ender Biotite Ore, an equivalent of Nether Quartz, added by the mod Quark.
Storage is a concept that becomes even more important in Modded Minecraft, as there is a much wider variety of items to store. This Quest Branch will cover the various options available for storage.

This upgraded chest, crafted with a chest and 8 iron ingots, can hold 54 stacks (as much as a double chest) in only a one block space. It can also be placed between double chests, allowing for much more compact storage.
This chest has 81 slots, 150% more than that of a double chest. It is crafted with 8 gold ingots and an iron chest.
This Chest can hold 108 slots of items, the most of any chest available in this modpack. That is, it can hold twice the items of a double chest or iron chest.

betterquesting:10.name:8: A Slope? Is this still Minecraft?

betterquesting:10.desc:8: This chest can hold just as much as the Diamond Chest, but also has the advantage of being Blast-Resistant, so those pesky creepers cannot damage it at all.
This chest, which holds 108 slots just like the diamond chest, allows you to view what is contained inside, without even opening it! Pretty cool, huh?

Welcome to ADG Omicron XII!! This quest book is meant to serve as a tutorial for those who may be new to Modded Minecraft. This chapter covers things you may already know, but also introduces the utility mods JEI and The One Probe, and the Content Mod Quark.
Now that you understand the bare minimum of modded Minecraft, let's start by introducing some mods that expand upon basic vanilla concepts, such as food, building, and storage.

This chapter will introduce several mods themed around technology and industry. As there are several of these types of mods available in this pack, There will be two of these chapters. This one will introduce "Low-Tech" mods such as Immersive Engineering and Tinkers' Construct, as well as the Mod Actually Additions as a gateway to higher-tech items.
Now that you have learned the lower-tech mods, This chapter will introduce some Higher-tech mods such as Thermal Expansion, RFTools, and AE2.

You may think that after the last two chapters, Modded Minecraft is all technology. However, this is simply not the case. Magic exists too, in mods such as Blood Magic, and it combines with tech in mods such as Embers and Botania. So get out there, and become a Master Archmage!!
